The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for motion recognition using RGB-D data, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNN), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multi-modal data, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses potential applications of the techniques in robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
